text.tspan: Built on AOSC OS technology, Afterglow is the
secret to keep vintage hardware running.
Our meticulously curated and tuned system
keeps you enjoying the devices you love.
Afterglow considers the following as primary architectures - with the
most comprehensive software features, updates, and security support.
The following architectures are supported with limited features:
Devices with hardware FPUs and NEONn
Workstations and servers with SPARC V9
For details on Afterglow's hardware compatibility and notes, as well as
hardware requirements, please refer to "Hardware Compatibility List",
"Known Issues", and "Hardware Requirements" in the manual.
Afterglow may be updated via the Internet. Please update your system
regularly for latest bugfixes, feature updates, and security patches.
Updated manuals and media may be released post-release, please fill
in the enclosed registration card upon receiving this media package.
The enclosed optical discs and diskettes are fragile and are subject to
damage, please use caution when handling and during storage.
